%% C4 dynamic — Consumer chain (at-least-once background-job lifecycle)
%% Source of truth: docs/adr/ + docs/architecture-brief.md — regenerate via /c4-designer, do not hand-edit
%% Generated: 2026-07-10
sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    participant BUS as Event Bus
    participant SRV as byteswarm Server
    participant DB as State Store
    participant TOOLS as External tools & processes

    BUS->>SRV: deliver event (subscribed type + workflowID) [NATS]
    SRV->>SRV: route to subscribed consumer(s)
    opt stateful consumer
        SRV->>DB: load consumer state [SQL]
        DB-->>SRV: state
    end
    SRV->>TOOLS: run command / launch process [OS exec]
    TOOLS-->>SRV: result / exit status
    opt stateful consumer
        SRV->>DB: persist updated state [SQL]
    end
    SRV->>BUS: publish derived event for downstream consumers [NATS]
    SRV->>BUS: ack processed event [NATS]
    Note over SRV,BUS: at-least-once — ack only after work + derived event persist, crash before ack causes redelivery (consumers idempotent)
